Project Description

This program reads numerical and categorical data from files, performs statistical analysis using Python fundamentals, applies object-oriented programming (OOP), handles errors, and saves results to a report file.

⸻

1. Variables & File Handling

Assumption
	•	data.csv → contains numerical data (e.g. student scores)
	•	categories.txt → contains categorical data (e.g. course names)

⸻

2. Error Handling
	•	Handles missing files
	•	Handles empty files
	•	Handles invalid (non-numeric) values

⸻

3. Functions

Functions are created to calculate:
	•	Total
	•	Average
	•	Minimum
	•	Maximum

⸻

4. Operators & Loops
	•	Arithmetic operators used
	•	for loop used to traverse the dataset

⸻

5. Conditional Statements
	•	Displays “High Performance” if average is above a threshold
	•	Otherwise displays “Needs Improvement”

⸻

6. Sets
	•	Extracts unique categorical values
	•	Counts total unique categories

⸻

7. Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)

A DataSet class is created with required methods.

⸻

8. Saving Results

Results are saved into report.txt

⸻

FULL PYTHON CODE

# GSE301 Data Science Assignment
# Author: Student
# Description: Data analysis using Python fundamentals

class DataSet:
    def __init__(self, data_file, category_file):
        self.data_file = data_file
        self.category_file = category_file
        self.data = []
        self.categories = set()
        self.total = 0
        self.average = 0
        self.minimum = None
        self.maximum = None

    # -------------------------------
    # Load Data
    # -------------------------------
    def load_data(self):
        try:
            with open(self.data_file, 'r') as file:
                for line in file:
                    value = line.strip()
                    if value:
                        self.data.append(float(value))
        except FileNotFoundError:
            print("Error: Data file not found.")
        except ValueError:
            print("Error: Invalid (non-numeric) data found.")

        try:
            with open(self.category_file, 'r') as file:
                for line in file:
                    category = line.strip()
                    if category:
                        self.categories.add(category)
        except FileNotFoundError:
            print("Error: Category file not found.")

    # -------------------------------
    # Statistical Calculations
    # -------------------------------
    def calculate_statistics(self):
        if not self.data:
            print("No data available for analysis.")
            return

        count = 0
        self.total = 0
        self.minimum = self.data[0]
        self.maximum = self.data[0]

        for value in self.data:
            self.total += value
            count += 1

            if value < self.minimum:
                self.minimum = value
            if value > self.maximum:
                self.maximum = value

        self.average = self.total / count

    # -------------------------------
    # Display Results
    # -------------------------------
    def display_results(self):
        print("----- DATA ANALYSIS RESULTS -----")
        print(f"Total: {self.total}")
        print(f"Average: {self.average}")
        print(f"Minimum: {self.minimum}")
        print(f"Maximum: {self.maximum}")

        if self.average >= 50:
            print("Performance: High Performance")
        else:
            print("Performance: Needs Improvement")

        print(f"Unique Categories: {len(self.categories)}")

    # -------------------------------
    # Save Results to File
    # -------------------------------
    def save_results(self):
        with open("report.txt", "w") as file:
            file.write("DATA ANALYSIS REPORT\n")
            file.write("---------------------\n")
            file.write(f"Total: {self.total}\n")
            file.write(f"Average: {self.average}\n")
            file.write(f"Minimum: {self.minimum}\n")
            file.write(f"Maximum: {self.maximum}\n")
            file.write(f"Unique Categories: {len(self.categories)}\n")

            if self.average >= 50:
                file.write("Performance: High Performance\n")
            else:
                file.write("Performance: Needs Improvement\n")

# -------------------------------
# Main Program Execution
# -------------------------------
dataset = DataSet("data.csv", "categories.txt")
dataset.load_data()
dataset.calculate_statistics()
dataset.display_results()
dataset.save_results()


